                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d561">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M)/7337: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-29T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 29, 1942—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>567. Your 723, June 19, 10 a.m.<note n="22" xml:id="d561fn22">Not printed.</note>
                    Pending completion of a full report on silk, Combined Raw Materials Board has
                    adopted an interim decision incorporating certain recommendations substance of
                    which is as follows:</p>
                <p>Available raw silk, waste silk, and noils in North and South America are to be at
                    the disposal of the United States and the United Kingdom is not to purchase in
                    those markets. Similarly, United States is to refrain from purchases in China,
                    India, Africa, and the Near and Middle East, where purchases are to be made by
                    the British only. Each country will notify the other of any available quantities
                    of silk in excess of its own requirements and will purchase for the other on
                    specific terms.</p>
                <p>You need not, therefore, pursue matter further for the present.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
